Products.Name: Weis Sorbet Lemon
Products.SupplyLimitMessage: 'Weis Sorbet Lemon' has a supply limit of 36. The quantity in your cart has been reduced accordingly. To purchase a larger quantity, please contact us on 1800 000 610. Please note we do not supply trade orders.
Products.RichDescription:
WEIS ICE CREAM LEMON SORBET 1 LTR

This classic, palate-cleansing Lemon Sorbet is made by Weis in the true Italian style. We use Australian lemon juice in just the right amount to make your tastebuds sit up and take notice. The result is a deliciously light and zesty treat that contains no preservatives, no dairy is 99% fat-free to be exact! Enjoy it between courses or as the perfect end to any meal. Lemon sorbet made the Weis way. How delightfully refreshing! Our delicously refreshing sorbet range is sure to be a hit in any home, particularly over the warmer summer months! Weis Sorbets are dairy free, made with real fruit, and have no artificial colours or flavours. Even better, they are absolutely delicious. Our classic sorbet flavours, like Australian Mango, Summer Berries and Refreshing Lemon, are a delightful and refreshing treat, great for after dinner or as a summertime snack. Or, if you are looking for something a little different, we now have a range of exotic sorbets. Weis Sorbet Exotics are sorbets with a twist! They are packed with interesting fruit and flavour combinations to create a truly surprising sorbet sensation! At Weis our products are based on recipes, so the focus is on the subtle blending of real ingredients and ultimately the taste. Our knowledge and expertise in sourcing and working with all different kinds of fruits, premium grade nuts and natural ingredients enables us to create unique combinations and taste experiences.

A deliciously light and zesty lemon sorbet made with real fruit.

Enjoy between courses or as the perfect crescendo to any meal

Dairy and gluten free

99% fat free and vegan friendly

A refreshing alternative to ice cream

Made in Australia since 1957

Products.RichDescription:
WEIS ICE CREAM SORBET MANGO 1 LTR

What does it take to deliver true-to-the-fruit ice cream mango taste? Well, it may seem a little obvious, but it’s nothing too tricky at all. Just lots and lots and lots of real mangoes. And not just any run-of-the-mill mango, we only use Kensington Prides. Sound special? It is. It’s hard to believe such a mouth-watering taste is possible. But here it is. The perfect mango experience without the mess, in a deliciously refreshing sorbet. Our sorbet range is sure to be a hit in any home, particularly over the warmer summer months! Weis Sorbets are dairy free, made with real fruit, and have no artificial colours or flavours. Even better, they are absolutely delicious. Our classic sorbet flavours, like Australian Mango, Summer Berries and Refreshing Lemon, are a delightful and refreshing treat, great for after dinner or as a summertime snack. Or, if you are looking for something a little different, we now have a range of exotic sorbets. Weis Sorbet Exotics are sorbets with a twist! They are packed with interesting fruit and flavour combinations to create a truly surprising sorbet sensation! At Weis our products are based on recipes, so the focus is on the subtle blending of real ingredients and ultimately the taste. Our knowledge and expertise in sourcing and working with all different kinds of fruits, premium grade nuts and natural ingredients enables us to create unique combinations and taste experiences.

Our Sorbet is made with Australian grown Kensington Pride mangoes ripened to perfection.

A refreshing and smooth sorbet to be enjoyed with fresh fruit, other desserts or simply on its own!

Dairy and gluten free

99% fat free and vegan friendly

A refreshing alternative to ice cream

Made in Australia since 1957

And not just any run-of-the-mill mango, we only use Kensington Prides. Sound special? It is. It’s hard to believe such a mouth-watering taste is possible. But here it is. The perfect mango experience without the mess, in a deliciously refreshing sorbet. Our sorbet range is sure to be a hit in any home, particularly over the warmer summer months! Weis Sorbets are dairy free, made with real fruit, and have no artificial colours or flavours. Even better, they are absolutely delicious. Our classic sorbet flavours, like Australian Mango, Summer Berries and Refreshing Lemon, are a delightful and refreshing treat, great for after dinner or as a summertime snack. Or, if you are looking for something a little different, we now have a range of exotic sorbets. Weis Sorbet Exotics are sorbets with a twist! They are packed with interesting fruit and flavour combinations to create a truly surprising sorbet sensation! At Weis our products are based on recipes, so the focus is on the subtle blending of real ingredients and ultimately the taste. Our knowledge and expertise in sourcing and working with all different kinds of fruits, premium grade nuts and natural ingredients enables us to create unique combinations and taste experiences.

Our Sorbet is made with Australian grown Kensington Pride mangoes ripened to perfection.

A refreshing and smooth sorbet to be enjoyed with fresh fruit, other desserts or simply on its own!

Dairy and gluten free

99% fat free and vegan friendly

A refreshing alternative to ice cream

Made in Australia since 1957

Products.RichDescription:
Ruffie Rustic Foods Portobello Mushroom Risotto With White Beans is meat-free, plant-based, vegan-friendly and a yummy source of protein. Freshly made and locked in goodness with Portobellos for extra flavour.
Ruffie Rustic Foods’ meals are a celebration of wholesome goodness.

Like all good risottos, we start with Arborio rice, then slowly stir and simmer while adding in coarsely chopped Portobello mushrooms, some broccoli florets and butter beans, then top with a scattering of parsley.

 
HINTS & TIPS

You’ll find me thick and creamy but if you want to make me cheesy, and your own parmesan – vegan or otherwise.
Meat Free
Vegan friendly
Plant Based
Good source of protein

Between World War 1 and World War 2, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted Street. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one horse power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well known brands such as Magnum, Viennetta, Paddle Pop, Cornetto, Gaytime, Calippo and Blue Ribbon.
Enjoy today!
